# TickTick Bridge — environment variable template
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env` in the same directory.
#   2. Fill in your real values in `.env`.
#   3. NEVER commit `.env` to git. It is gitignored.
#
# SECURITY RULES:
#   - Tokens are runtime secrets. They must not appear in any markdown,
#     planning doc, commit message, or code comment.
#   - `.env` is for local machine use only. It is not shared via git.
#   - If credentials are suspected to have leaked into git, rotate them
#     immediately via the TickTick Developer Portal and scrub git history.
#
# HOW TO REGISTER A DEVELOPER APP:
#   - Go to https://developer.ticktick.com/
#   - Create an app to obtain client_id and client_secret.
#   - Set the redirect URI to match TICKTICK_REDIRECT_URI below.
#   - This step is manual and must be done by the user.

# OAuth credentials from TickTick Developer Portal
TICKTICK_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
TICKTICK_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# Must match the redirect URI registered in the Developer Portal
TICKTICK_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/callback

# Optional: default TickTick project/list ID to export tasks into.
# Leave blank to create a new list per week automatically.
TICKTICK_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID=

# TOKEN STORAGE POLICY:
# Access tokens and refresh tokens are NOT stored in .env.
# They are stored in .ticktick/ticktick_token.json (gitignored) by:
#   python tools/auth_ticktick.py login
# Do not add token fields here.
